      <h3 class="blogh3">National Savings Certificate (NSC): A Safe Way to Grow Your Savings</h3>
      <p>If you’re looking for a low-risk, tax-saving investment that guarantees steady returns, the National Savings Certificate (NSC) is a solid choice. Backed by the Government of India, NSC is designed for conservative savers who want to grow their money safely.</p>
       
      <h3 class="blogh3">What is NSC? </h3>
      <p>The National Savings Certificate is a fixed-income investment scheme offered by the post office. It is primarily meant for small to mid-level investors looking for guaranteed returns over 5 years, along with tax benefits.</p>
      <h3 class="blogh3">Key Features of NSC: </h3>
      <p><b>Interest Rate (Currently 7.7%) :</b> The interest rate is fixed by the government and remains the same throughout the 5-year tenure. As of now, it is 7.7% compounded annually.</p>
      <p><b>Investment Limit:</b> Minimum investment is ₹1,000. There’s no maximum limit, but only up to ₹1.5 lakh per year qualifies for tax benefits under Section 80C.</p>
      <p><b>Tenure:</b> Fixed for 5 years. Funds can only be withdrawn after maturity, except in special cases like the holder’s death.</p>
      <p><b>Compounded Annually:</b> The interest is compounded annually but paid out only at the end of 5 years along with the principal.</p>
      <p><b>Tax Benefits :</b> Investment qualifies for deduction under Section 80C. However, interest earned is taxable as per your income slab.</p>
       

